titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the William Paul Wreden collection
titlestmt.author: compiled by Janet Elaine Gertz

publicationstmt.publisher: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on Tuesday April 23, 2019 at 07:14

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The collection consists of approximately two hundred letters and several other documents, most signed by English political figures and authors of the nineteenth and early twentieth centuries.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: William Paul Wreden Collection (MS 564). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: These papers consist of an autograph collection composed of over two hundred letters and a few other documents, most signed by English political figures and authors of the nineteenth and early twentieth centuries. The materials have been arranged in alphabetical order.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: William P. Wreden was a rare book dealer and publisher. He entered the rare book business in 1937, and was also the owner of Pinole Land & Cattle Company, California. He published Bibliography of Valentine Greatrakes .

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Unpublished materials authored or otherwise produced by the creator(s) of this collection are in the public domain. There are no restrictions on use.
